Key Match Events: Dodgers first baseman Freddie Freeman rolled his right ankle while attempting to beat out a ground ball in the seventh inning, leaving the game. The Dodgers scored five runs in the seventh inning en route to a 7-2 victory over the Padres, clinching their 11th National League West title in 12 seasons.
Post-Match Reflections: The Dodgers clinched their 11th National League West title with the win.
